cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SI

This paper deals with efficient inference algorithms for high-order potentials in graphical models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The use of cardinality potentials is also a common technique in this field. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of belief propagation, which is a common technique in the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
